While working on this project, I learned that there are so many aspects to creating a functional, accessible, and user-friendly app. 
We used Gemini to help us code the main HTML and Python codes, and we were the ones that implemented everything into one packet, an .exe
file using PyInstaller. I also realized that making an app isn't enough, I have to consider the people that will use it. We added the
light/dark mode feature so that people that are sensitive to light are accounted for. We limited user input so that it would be user-friendly
and easier to use. Limiting user input also limits possible mistakes, so errors will rarely occur.
